  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Caroline Weston is sending the long expected letters from Haiti. She gives explanations of certain dressmaking problems, which she illustrates with small, thumbnail sketches in the letter. Anne Warren Weston has decided to go to New York and Caroline has also decided to go; she wishes that Deborah Weston could manage to go. Wendell Phillips told Caroline that he will keep the proposed evening free for New Bedford.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Caroline Weston continues the letter by writing crosswise in pencil. She writes: &quot;Mrs. [Eliza Lee Cabot] Follen&apos;s life of her husband is excellent &amp; I am moved to tears...by the facts it contains.</subfield>
  </datafield>
